The paper deals with dynamic algorithms for maintaining low-stretch trees, which is a problem in graph theory and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM). The paper also uses techniques from computational geometry (cs.CG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) to achieve its results. Additionally, the paper mentions applications in solvers for linear systems, which could fall under scientific computing (cs.SI).
